# Jump Game IX Notes

## Standard Problem Idea

Given:

* `nums[]` → heights
* `cost[]` → jump cost

Goal:
Reach last index with minimum total cost.

## Valid Jump Rules

Jump from `i` to `j` (`i < j`) if:

### Rule 1 — Valley Jump

```text
nums[i] <= nums[j]
```

and all elements between them are smaller than `nums[i]`.

### Rule 2 — Mountain Jump

```text
nums[i] > nums[j]
```

and all elements between them are greater or equal to `nums[i]`.

## Standard Approach

* Dynamic Programming
* Monotonic Stack
* Minimum Cost Transitions

Usually:

```text
dp[j] = min(dp[j], dp[i] + cost[j])
```

