# My Prefix/Suffix Based Observation

## Precomputation

### Prefix Maximum

```text
pref[i] = max(0...i)
```

### Suffix Minimum

```text
suf[i] = min(i...n-1)
```

These create a valid range/corridor.

---

## Greedy Backward Pass

Maintain:

```text
far = index of smaller future candidate
```

Transition:

```java
if(nums[far] < pref[i] && nums[far] >= suf[i])
    ans[i] = ans[far];
else
    ans[i] = pref[i];
```

Update:

```java
if(nums[i] < nums[far])
    far = i;
```

---

# Important Observation

This solution does NOT solve standard Jump Game IX.

Why?

* Standard problem is DP + Monotonic Stack.
* It minimizes jump cost.
* My approach only analyzes prefix/suffix range behavior.

So this becomes more of:

* Greedy
* Range inheritance
* Prefix/Suffix boundary analysis

rather than shortest path DP.
